result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Proceedings held on September 5, 2014 - Original transcript filed in 14CF113.

Defendant Kaylynn Marie Samplaski in court/custody (on new charges) with attorney Gary S. Cirilli.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called  11:35 am State have resolution on 13CF165 plead to count 1 & 4 as alleged DRI all other counts with 1 year jail on each count concurrent to each other and costs on each count Cirilli agrees, pleads NC to count 1 & 4, 13CF228 count 1 w/hold and place on probation 3  years consecutive to jail in 13CF165, Cirilli agrees, pleads NC to count 1 and court count 2 DRI, 13CF240 plead to counts 1-6 $738.81 restitution plus surcharge and costs on each count, Cirilli agrees, pleads NC to counts 1-6, court counts 7-10 DRI, 13CF241 plead to count 1 $653.43 restitution from bond on other cases plus costs/surcharge, Cirili agrees and pleads NC to count 1, court DRI counts 2-6, 14CF54 plead to count 1 w/held and place on probation for 5 years (concurrent to probation in 13CF280 and  consecutive to 13CF165 jail time - 1 year jail as a conditional time consecutive to 13CF165, discussion on restitution - Cirilli wants state to check on the figures and then he would have 15 days to object/agree, victims is in court and states $5000 paid back pleads NC to count 1 counts 2-4 DRI by court.14CF55 DRI completely court dismisses. 13CV91 state moves to dismiss outright for stated reasons. Court file motion within 10 days. 14CF113 - INIT - has complaint waive reading. Set for PH. 09-17-14 @ 2:30 pm. State asks for bond to continue @ $5000. Recall the bond matter after plea/sentencing. Court bond posted by someone other than Ms Samplaski. State not aware of that. 14CF81 still waiting on results from state lab. Set for JT on 10-13-14. State believes will resolve. Bond continued on 14CF81. State wants to take any available money from bond to be repaid to FC Drug Task Force $410 and then modify bond on the new case and will dismiss if the money is paid back. Danette Gilligan makes statement that Shelby C has been repaid the $5000 and that the money would be owed to Danette. Court will not consider the consolidation of the Langlade county cases. State has complied with victim notification and victim's are in court. Court has reviewed both of the letters that has been sent by 1 of the victims. Court has also read the victim impact statement on 14CF113. Court finds defendant guility of all charges in which she plead too freely, voluntarily and intelligently by entering her plea and waiving her right to JT, factual basis, adjudges guility of all counts as plead too. State final argument asks to use bonds for restitution and follow the joint recommendation. Discussion on issue of bond going to cases court will not apply bond as she didn't pay the bond money other parties posted the bond. Cirilli final argument believes that $1000 from Langlade county case can be applied to Forest county cases follow proposal. Samplaski makes statement. Court proceed to sentencing after addressing the issue of some of the elements of charges Cirilli/Samplaski agree to proceed. Court sentence to following. Victims do not want to make statements. 13CF165 count 1 - 1 year jail (huber, good time, co service 973.03(3)), costs/surcharges take from bond any transfer any balances to other cases. Count 4 1 year jail consecutive to count 1 costs/surcharges plus DNA surcharge. 13CF228 count 1 w/hold sentence and place on probation for 3 years consecutive to jail in 13CF165. with conditions of obtain GED, random urnalysis tests by law enforcement, no consume/possess or entry, AODA and follow thru, NA/AA or similar meeting 2 x per week, emp/school with verbage 3 jobs per week, 10 different employers each month, costs, 1 year FC jail consecutive to 13CF165, 150 hrs co service. 13CF240 costs count 1 - 6, restitution paid w/in 60 days of today, commitment order if fail to pay and will be consecutive to any jail sentence currently serving. 13CF241 costs only restitution paid w/in 60 days and failure to pay not to exceed 6 months consecutive to all other jail that she is serving. 14CF54 -  w/hold sentence and place on probation for 5 years concurrent with 13CF228 same conditions as other cases plus 150 hrs co service, 1 year jail consecutive to 13CF228  (stayed) if employed and defendant must petition either court to appoint conservator appointed by either tribal court or circuit court and can not be family member. If both of these conditions are met then does not have to serve the final 1 year conditional jail time. If AODA indicates inpatient treatment (substitute for job if in treatment or full time school) or if conservator appoint done (must be done prior to release from 13CF228)  then 1 year conditional jail time on 14CF54 would not be served. Participate in parenting class on both probation cases. Follow all rules of the CHIPS cases and condtions for return of the children. Cirilli don't believe jail credit but will check and submit stipulation if any is coming. 13CF165 will get credit. All other credit will be if revoked. State to determine restitution w/in 10 days and Cirilli 15 days if no object JOC will be amended to indicate what state recited in court on 13CF241. Voting/firearm and appeal rights given.
